**Q3: What is Pigeon and why use it?**

**A:** Pigeon is a code generator that turns a Dart interface declaration into type-safe channel code on both sides (Dart + Kotlin + Swift + optionally C++/Java/Objective-C). Without Pigeon, you write raw `MethodChannel('com.myapp/foo').invokeMethod('bar', args)` — untyped, stringly-typed, easy to break. With Pigeon, you write:
```dart
@HostApi()
abstract class BatteryApi {
  int getBatteryLevel();
}
```
Run `pigeon` — you get typed classes on both sides. **Wins:** compile-time type safety, generated codecs, refactor-safe (renaming a method updates both sides), documentation-friendly. **Modern Flutter apps that write custom channels should use Pigeon.**
